PAGE 1: The Core Problem & The Zaki Ledger Solution

The Current Reality for UK Bookkeepers
A typical UK bookkeeping team loses 4 to 8 hours per week, per staff member, to manual invoice data entry, line-item extraction, and manual verification.
While platforms like Xero and QuickBooks provide basic built-in document capture tools, they fall short in real-world accounting workflows:
Static OCR: They can pull out basic totals, but they do not understand complex multi-page invoices or messy line-item distributions.
No Error Guidance: They don’t tell you where an invoice extraction might be risky, forcing your staff to manually cross-check every single field anyway.
No Long-Term Memory: Every time a client receives an invoice from a repeat supplier, standard software treats it as a brand-new layout. You lose valuable time re-correcting the same field structures month after month.

The Zaki Ledger Evolution
Zaki Ledger is an AI-native accounting automation engine built strictly for professional bookkeeping firms. It replaces manual typing with an autonomous, high-accuracy verification loop:
Multimodal Visual Reasoning: Powered by high-tier artificial intelligence, the system reads invoices contextually, handling blurry mobile receipts, complex data tables, and mixed tax codes with human-like comprehension.
Active Confidence Scoring: Every extracted field features a visible certainty score (e.g., "98% confident"). Your staff immediately spot which 5% of entries require a quick glance, bypassing the 95% that are flawless.
Per-Supplier Learning Moat: The platform actively remembers user corrections. When you fix a mapping rule for a specific supplier, Zaki Ledger updates its internal ledger. Future invoices from that vendor are parsed near-instantly with zero human touches.



PAGE 2: The Core Workflow & Integration Pipeline

How It Operates in Your Office
Your staff change nothing about their current accounting software. Zaki Ledger acts as an intelligence bridge sitting directly in front of your client accounts.

[Invoice Received] ➔ [Zaki Ledger AI Parser] ➔ [1-Click Approval View] ➔ [Instant Xero Draft]
Ingestion: Clients forward invoices to a dedicated e-mail inbox, or your staff upload bulk PDFs and image formats onto a simple touch-optimized desktop interface.
Context Extraction: The dual-model engine runs the payload, checks historical templates for that specific vendor, calculates tax structures, and presents a minified JSON summary.
The "Yes/No/Correct" Ledger: Instead of typing fields out manually, your bookkeepers review a clean screen. They simply tap Approve, make a minor correction that trains the system permanently, or reject the entry.
Instant Platform Sync: On approval, the system triggers a background webhook via the Xero/QuickBooks API, passing the finalized structure into the client’s Draft Bills folder automatically.



